point : the concept of parenthood in the context of donor assist conception be complicate . is someone who donate an egg or some sperm really a parent ? shouldn't parent mean the one who care for you a a baby , get up in the night for you , saw you through teethe and childhood illness , and work hard to give you food , shelter and the best life they be able to provide ? in the case of child seek the mother who give them up for adoption , this be permissible specifically because of the relationship build up during pregnancy and birth1 . in the case of sperm donor , 'whether for money or out of altruism , the father have go into a cubicle and masturbate into a container . there be a difference'1 . as such , give that donor never actually meet or speak to the real parent or the actual child , the situation be not at all like adoption or even surrogacy . it be more like blood donation , and therefore give the recipient no right over the donor . 1 berlins , m . 2006 , april 5 . children's right to find their sperm donor father . retrieved july 6 , 2011 , from the guardian 1 
counterpoint : sperm and egg donor be biological , and therefore the only objectively true , parent . therefore , they have to accept that a child conceive use their material assume 50 of their dna , and inevitably thereafter will be link to them . donors who enter into the process must therefore accept that child be naturally go to be curious about where half of themselves originate . as olivia merricks , who use a sperm donor to have her daughter zannah , argue , 'i think people should only be donor if they understand that need to know more about yourself'1 . nowhere else in the law be child deny the right to know who their parent be if the information be available . this reflect the widely hold , and very natural , notion that learn about yourself be one of the fundamental driving force of life . we ask our parent question not just to know about their life , but to understand how we come to be . it be to our parent that we direct such question specifically because we share their gene . as such , donor cannot deny they be true parent . 
