point : sperm and egg donor have a right to remain anonymous . having go out of their way to provide a mean for a couple to have the child they otherwise could not have have , they deserve their wish to be respect in return . the unveiling of their identity and , likely , contact from the child would cause psychological harm at least equal to that of the offspring1 . there should be no hierarchy regard whose right be more important , disclosure should only be permit if both party be happy to do so . in the united states , for example , when sign up with donor bank , donor be able to 'make it clear' they don't want to be find by sign a waiver of anonymity2 . if donor wish to sign that form and retain their privacy , that right should not be take from them , regardless of the child's wish . donors should be entitle to move on with their life and not fear be track by offspring they neither ask for , nor wanted3 . 1 berlins , m . 2006 , april 5 . children's right to find their sperm donor father . retrieved july 6 , 2011 , from the guardian 1 2 lehmann haupt , r . 2010 , march 1 . anonymous anymore ? retrieved july 13 , 2011 , from slate : 8 3 essig , t . 2011 , june 30 . balancing the rights of donor offspring with those of donors : but what about parents ? retrieved july 6 , 2011 , from forbes : 9 
